His name was Shoko Asahara, and he was the founder of Japan’s most deadly cult, Aum Shinrikyo.

00:02:53.752 --> 00:02:57.499
A cult always starts with one person, a persuasive,

00:02:57.829 --> 00:03:01.699
charismatic but deluded and often dangerous individual.

00:03:02.739 --> 00:03:08.059
And in the case of Aum Shinrikyo, this individual was Shoko Asahara.

00:03:09.309 --> 00:03:14.389
This wasn’t his birth name; he was born Chizuo Matsumoto, and would

